During a press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre discussed a range of topics. She highlighted the recent Presidential Medals of Honor and Freedom ceremonies, where Vietnam veterans and other individuals were recognized for their service. She also announced nearly $1 billion in funding from President Biden's Bipartisan Infrastructure Law to modernize 85 airports across the United States. Jean-Pierre criticized Senator Mitch McConnell for holding hostage the Bipartisan Innovation Act, which aims to strengthen America's competitive edge with China. She emphasized the importance of passing the bill and called on McConnell to act. Jean-Pierre also addressed the cases of Brittney Griner and Paul Whelan, who are being wrongfully detained in Russia. She stated that the administration is committed to bringing them home safely and is using all available means to do so. Additionally, Jean-Pierre discussed the President's ongoing efforts to protect women's rights, including his support for codifying Roe v. Wade into law. She mentioned that the President plans to hold a larger ceremony for the recently signed gun legislation and expressed his commitment to further gun reform, including a ban on assault weapons. Finally, Jean-Pierre addressed questions about the IRS Commissioner, the departure of the White House Communications Director, and the potential appointment of a new Secret Service Director.